A bank is permitted to open and operate the following accounts without any of the restrictions placed in terms of paragraph 78 to paragraph 86:
(1) Specific accounts which are stipulated under various statutes and specific instructions of other regulators / regulatory departments / Central and State Governments. An indicative list of such accounts is given below:
